The paper discusses the development of a neural network model for regression problems, which falls under the category of machine learning. Specifically, the paper proposes a robust stochastic configuration network (RSCN) with kernel density estimation (KDE) to handle noisy and uncertain data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions the use of the RSCN model for image processing, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
